<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD9FF87B5B9FA3BFEBEFA45" blockId="21.[189,310,1502,1528]" box="[189,310,1502,1528]" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFD9FF87B5B9FA3BFEBEFA45" bold="true" box="[189,310,1502,1528]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="95" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B5B9FA3BFEBEFA45" bold="true" box="[189,310,1502,1528]" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD9FF87B5B9F9E8FE0CF92C" blockId="21.[188,1400,1549,1681]" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">
This species is close to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD9FF87B70AF9E8FD20F99A" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1924" box="[526,680,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlaensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B70AF9E8FD20F99A" box="[526,680,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">S. simlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
owing to a similar structure, sculpture of the body and the fact that the females morphologically are difficult to distinguish, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD9FF87B6FEF9D5FB10F9F7" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[1018,1176,1584,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B6FEF9D5FB10F9F7" box="[1018,1176,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">S. iridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a slightly less transverse head (1.1 times as wide as long vs 1.2) and entirely red legs (at least femora black or brownish in 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD9FF87B5DFF992FEFAF92D" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1924" box="[219,370,1654,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlaensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B5DFF992FEFAF92D" box="[219,370,1654,1681]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">S. simlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
