<subSubSection id="C349651EFFD9FF85B5B9F8AEFEB1FD85" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="21" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD9FF87B5B9F8AEFE1BF8D8" blockId="21.[189,403,1867,1893]" box="[189,403,1867,1893]" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFD9FF87B5B9F8AEFE1BF8D8" bold="true" box="[189,403,1867,1893]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="95" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B5B9F8AEFE1BF8D8" bold="true" box="[189,403,1867,1893]" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">Descriptive notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD9FF87B5B9F89CFED7F867" blockId="21.[189,1398,1913,2010]" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">
Wings with weak yellowish or brownish darkening; hind wing with basal vein strongly curved with the angle between basal (
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B4E2F878FE76F80B" box="[486,510,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">M</emphasis>
) and cubital (
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD9FF87B7A7F878FD4DF80A" box="[675,709,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="95">Cu</emphasis>
) veins ca 90°, costal margin with five hamuli. Preoccipital carina absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDAFF84B5EEFEECFECDFE9E" blockId="22.[189,1398,265,432]" box="[234,325,265,291]" pageId="22" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDAFF84B5EEFEECFECDFE9E" bold="true" box="[234,325,265,291]" pageId="22" pageNumber="96">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDAFF85B5B9FEC9FB92FE6E" blockId="22.[189,1398,265,432]" lastBlockId="23.[189,1400,265,467]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="22" pageNumber="96">
Total body length 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFDAFF84B4A5FECEFE77FEFB" box="[417,511,299,326]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="96" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFDAFF84B710FEC9FD0CFEFB" box="[532,644,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1923,1949]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-80@22.[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Sphecodes iridipennis Smith, 1879. Holotype, ♀ (NHMUK 013380317). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in frontal view. C. Labels. D. Mesosoma in dorsal view. E. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars: A, D–E = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705346/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="96">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Head weakly transverse, at most 1.1 times as wide as long (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFDAFF84B5C2FEAAFEBBFED4" box="[198,307,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1923,1949]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-80@22.[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Sphecodes iridipennis Smith, 1879. Holotype, ♀ (NHMUK 013380317). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in frontal view. C. Labels. D. Mesosoma in dorsal view. E. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars: A, D–E = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705346/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="96">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
); vertex not elevated as seen in frontal view; F1 and F2 transverse, 0.5–0.6 times as long as wide, F3 0.8 times as long as wide; clypeus with punctures separated by 1–3 puncture diameters; ocello-ocular area with fine punctures separated by 1–3 puncture diameters; face and gena with sparse pubescence. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum with punctures (15–20 μm) separated by 1–4 puncture diameters (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFDBFF85B445FEC9FE27FEFB" box="[321,431,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1923,1949]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-80@22.[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Sphecodes iridipennis Smith, 1879. Holotype, ♀ (NHMUK 013380317). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in frontal view. C. Labels. D. Mesosoma in dorsal view. E. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars: A, D–E = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705346/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
); hypoepimeral area coarsely reticulate; metafemur weakly enlarged in proximal half, maximum width 0.35 times its length; legs red. Propodeal triangle (metapostnotum) with coarse longitudinal wrinkles and shiny interspaces. Metasomal terga scarcely punctate, T1 impunctate, remaining terga basally with sparse fine setal pores (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFDBFF85B622FE73FC06FE0D" box="[806,910,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1923,1949]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-80@22.[189,1398,533,1879]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Sphecodes iridipennis Smith, 1879. Holotype, ♀ (NHMUK 013380317). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in frontal view. C. Labels. D. Mesosoma in dorsal view. E. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars: A, D–E = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705346/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
); marginal zones impunctate; terga red to red-brownish apically, pygidial plate 0.7 times as wide as metabasitarsus.
</paragraph>
