<subSubSection id="C349651EFFDBFF85B5B9FDBAFD06FD76" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDBFF85B5B9FDBAFEDEFDC4" blockId="23.[189,342,607,633]" box="[189,342,607,633]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFDBFF85B5B9FDBAFEDEFDC4" bold="true" box="[189,342,607,633]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B5B9FDBAFEDEFDC4" bold="true" box="[189,342,607,633]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDBFF85B5B9FD68FD06FD76" blockId="23.[189,1398,653,716]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">
Himalayas: 
<collectingRegion id="4997F877FFDBFF85B44FFD68FE57FD1A" box="[331,479,653,679]" country="India" name="Uttarakhand" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">Uttarakhand</collectingRegion>
, Northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3447605FFDBFF85B75BFD68FD17FD1A" box="[607,671,653,679]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">India</collectingCountry>
. The record of the species from 
<collectingRegion id="4997F877FFDBFF85B125FD68FB70FD1A" box="[1057,1272,653,679]" country="India" name="Himachal Pradesh" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">Himachal Pradesh</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3447605FFDBFF85B00DFD68FAC1FD15" box="[1289,1353,653,680]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">India</collectingCountry>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFDBFF85B5BAFD54FD88FD71" author="Saini M. S. &amp; Rathor V. S." box="[190,512,689,716]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" pagination="134 - 166" refId="ref18996" refString="Saini M. S. &amp; Rathor V. S. 2012. A species checklist of family Halictidae (Hymenoptera: Apoidea) along with keys to its subfamilies, genera &amp; subgenera from India. International Journal of Environmental Sciences 3 (1): 134 - 166." type="journal article" year="2012">Saini &amp; Rathor (2012: 162)</bibRefCitation>
is doubtful.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C349651EFFDBFF85B5B9FD17FD94FB91" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDBFF85B5B9FD17FEA7FCB1" blockId="23.[189,303,754,780]" box="[189,303,754,780]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFDBFF85B5B9FD17FEA7FCB1" bold="true" box="[189,303,754,780]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B5B9FD17FEA7FCB1" bold="true" box="[189,303,754,780]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDBFF85B5B9FCC4FD09FC3F" blockId="23.[189,1399,801,898]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">
Since we could not clearly differentiate between females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFDBFF85B681FCC4FBAAFC86" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[901,1058,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B681FCC4FBAAFC86" box="[901,1058,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">S. iridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFDBFF85B159FCC4FB7DFC86" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1924" box="[1117,1269,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlaensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B159FCC4FB7DFC86" box="[1117,1269,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">S. simlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except by their relative head length and coloration, more specimens should be studied (including the male finding) to make a decision on their synonymy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFDBFF85B5B9FC4DFD94FB91" blockId="23.[189,1398,936,1069]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">
The specimens recorded as 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFDBFF85B709FC4CFD24FC7F" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[525,684,936,963]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B709FC4CFD24FC7F" box="[525,684,936,963]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">S. iridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Chapra (
<collectingCountry id="F3447605FFDBFF85B665FC4DFC29FC7E" box="[865,929,936,963]" name="India" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">India</collectingCountry>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFDBFF85B6DFFC4DFAC1FC7E" author="Rajkumar M. B. &amp; Dey D." box="[987,1353,936,963]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" pagination="1839 - 1849" refId="ref18937" refString="Rajkumar M. B. &amp; Dey D. 2016. Identification and description of Indian parasitic bee genus Sphecodes Latreille 1804, (Halictidae: Hymenoptera). Journal of Applied and Natural Science 8 (4): 1839 - 1849. https: // doi. org / 10.31018 / jans. v 8 i 4.1051" type="journal article" year="2016">Rajkumar &amp; Dey (2016: 1847</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 3) belong to another species. Unlike the 
<typeStatus id="54E88837FFDBFF85B7B7FC29FC92FC5B" box="[691,794,972,998]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
this specimen, re-described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFDBFF85B198FC29FAB5FC5B" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1879" box="[1180,1341,972,998]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B198FC29FAB5FC5B" box="[1180,1341,972,998]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">S. iridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has more transverse head (1.3 times as wide as long) and possibly belongs to the undescribed female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFDBFF85B5B9FBF6FD90FB91" authority="Bluthgen, 1927" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[189,536,1042,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaprensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFDBFF85B5B9FBF6FED0FB91" box="[189,344,1042,1069]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="97">S. chaprensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFDBFF85B464FBF7FD90FB91" author="Bluthgen P." box="[352,536,1042,1068]" pageId="23" pageNumber="97" pagination="23 - 112" refId="ref17172" refString="Bluthgen P. 1927. Beitrage zur Systematik der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. III. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 53 (1 / 3): 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1927">Blüthgen, 1927</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
